<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                    <head>No. 396.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Curry</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 6, 1886</date>.
                            (Received October 6.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Curry informs Mr. Bayard that the collection of discriminating duties
                        will continue as in the past on the products of foreign countries which are
                        shipped to Cuba and Porto Rico from ports of the United States.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>